Police confiscated 31,000 mandrax tablets after a high-speed chase in Kraaifontein. CAPE TOWN - A suspected drug peddler is expected in court in connection with a R1 million drug bust. Acting on a tip-off, police officers made the bust in Kraaifontein on Monday. They confiscated 31,000 mandrax tablets after a high-speed chase. The police's Noloyiso Rwexana says: "They managed to stop the vehicle. A 26-year-old suspect was arrested and will face charges in relation to dealing in drugs."